Name: petey
Comment: Petey is a handsome bantam rooster looking for his forever home!Have you heard about our adoption special?During the month of October, you choose the amount you pay for an adoption (at least $50 suggested) and what your adoption supports. Your donation can assist with special medical care, food & supplies, and owner support for the residents of Santa Cruz County and their companion animals. Your support allows us to save hundreds of additional animal lives and support families and pets in need. Whatever you decide to donate in place of an adoption fee, your new pet will be spayed or neutered, microchipped, vaccinated, and treated for parasites. We want to get every pet off to a healthy start in a new home!

Name: black saddle eclipse "diego"
Comment: Black Saddle Eclipse (aka "Diego"), is a gentle older horse surrendered to us when his previous guardian was unable to continue to provide for him. Diego loads easily, travels quite well, and has been re-gaining weight and muscle while staying at an equine foster home. He's had his feet done, his teeth floated, and he's feeling MUCH better than when he arrived! If you're looking for a companion horse, a therapy horse, or you're just interested in providing a comfortable, safe, and healthy "retirement home" for a beautiful and sweet-natured registered palomino American Morgan, please reach out to us so we can put you in touch with Diego's foster mom to arrange a visit and some discussion. This handsome gentleman has been through a lot, so we want to find him a good, loving forever home!

Name: poppy
Comment: Poppy arrived to the shelter with an injured wing, and has made a full recovery!Poppy is wearing an ID band which had untraceable information, so the medical team helped treat the inuries. They are patiently waiting to be adopted to someone with room in an aviary to let them spread their wings.

Name: bela
Comment: Greetings earth dwellers! My name is "Bela", like Bela Lugosi.. My previous owners did not handle me much, as they did not seem to know how to co exist with a birdie like me. I like to fly, and need to connect on a 'higher plane"  (haha) I love the finer things in life:  clean air, fresh organic veggies and Evian in my bottle. It's been really lonely in my old tiny cage, so some space and perhaps another fair feathered friend is in order. If you know birds, then I think we will get along just fine!

Name: franklin
Comment: Do you have a soft spot for the littles in the world? Meet Franklin* a very petite  juvenille mouse that came into the shelter. He is inquistive, gentle and would make a  lovely little companion. He is very small right now- currently working on his size and would need an experienced person to handle him due to his delicate nature. Mice make excellent companions, they are clean, friendly and trainable! Prior to adoption, make sure you are brushed up on your *mouse ettiquite* and come see this adorable little fella!
